Design an implementation plan for the Chat.svelte component in a Svelte 5 / SvelteKit project (the "Claudia" interactive fiction game).

## Current state

`Chat.svelte` is a stub that only renders the active chat's name in an `<h2>`. It needs to become a full message-rendering component.

## Types (from `src/lib/types.ts`)
```ts
export type Markdown = string & { readonly _brand: 'Markdown' };
export const md = (s: string): Markdown => s as Markdown;
export type Image = string;
export type UTCTime = Date;

export interface ChatUser {
  name: string;
  profilePicture: Image;  // empty string in seed data, CSS fallback background
  status: 'active' | 'away' | 'busy' | 'offline';
  statusText: Markdown;
}

export type ChatComponentState = ChatUser & {
  messages: { role: 'user' | 'partner'; text: Markdown; time: UTCTime }[];
};

export type ChatAppState = {
  chats: ChatComponentState[];
  player: ChatUser;
  currentlySelected: number;
};
```

## State (`src/lib/state.svelte.ts`)
- Singleton `appState: ChatAppState` using Svelte 5 `$state()` rune
- `appState.chats[0]` is Claudia (active, no seed messages)
- Other chats have one seed partner message each
- `appendPartnerMessage(index, text)` adds partner messages

## Existing Selector.svelte patterns to follow
- `formatTime(date)` helper: HH:MM if today, "Mon DD" if older
- Avatar: `<img src={chat.profilePicture} alt={chat.name} class="avatar">` with `background: #ccc` CSS fallback
- Status dot: `<span class="status-dot status--{chat.status}"></span>` with 4 color classes

## Page layout context (`+page.svelte`)
```svelte
<main class="conversation">
  <Chat />
  <Input />
</main>
```
And the CSS:
```css
.conversation {
  flex: 1;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}
/* Chat scrollable area expands; Input stays anchored at the bottom */
.conversation :global(.chat) {
  flex: 1;
  overflow-y: auto;
}
```
So `.chat` must flex-expand and scroll. The outer container handles overflow-y.

## Testing patterns (from `Selector.svelte.spec.ts`)
```ts
import { page } from 'vitest/browser';
