## Files to Change

| File | Action |
|---|---|
| `src/lib/time.ts` | **Create** ÔÇö extract `formatTime` from Selector (DRY: needed in both Chat and Selector) |
| `src/lib/Selector.svelte` | **Edit** ÔÇö replace inline `formatTime` with `import { formatTime } from './time.js'` |
| `src/lib/Chat.svelte` | **Replace** ÔÇö full implementation (header + message list) |
| `src/lib/Chat.svelte.spec.ts` | **Create** ÔÇö browser tests following Selector.svelte.spec.ts patterns |
| `src/routes/page.svelte.spec.ts` | **Edit** ÔÇö update the broken `h2` heading check to match new header structure |

## Implementation (TDD order: tests first, then feature)

### 1. `src/lib/time.ts` (new)

```ts
/** Format a message time: HH:MM if today, else "Mon DD". */
export function formatTime(date: Date): string {
    const now = new Date();
    const sameDay =
        date.getFullYear() === now.getFullYear() &&
        date.getMonth() === now.getMonth() &&
        date.getDate() === now.getDate();
    if (sameDay) {
        return date.toLocaleTimeString([], { hour: '2-digit', minute: '2-digit' });
    }
    return date.toLocaleDateString([], { month: 'short', day: 'numeric' });
}
```

Then in `Selector.svelte`: remove the inline definition, add `import { formatTime } from './time.js';`.

### 2. `src/lib/Chat.svelte` ÔÇö full component

**Script:**
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
    import { appState } from './state.svelte.js';
    import { formatTime } from './time.js';

    const chat = $derived(appState.chats[appState.currentlySelected]);

    // bind:this on <ul> ÔÇö plain let, not $state, since we just call methods on it
    let messagesEl: HTMLUListElement;

    // Re-runs after DOM update whenever message count or selected chat changes
    $effect(() => {
        chat.messages.length;
        messagesEl?.scrollTo({ top: messagesEl.scrollHeight });
    });
</script>
```

**Template:**
```svelte
<section class="chat">
    <header class="chat-header">
        <div class="avatar-wrap">
            <img src={chat.profilePicture} alt={chat.name} class="avatar" />
            <span class="status-dot status--{chat.status}"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="chat-info">
            <span class="chat-name">{chat.name}</span>
            <span class="chat-status-text">{chat.statusText}</span>
        </div>
    </header>

    {#if chat.messages.length === 0}
        <p class="empty-state">No messages yet. Say something.</p>
    {:else}
        <ul class="message-list" bind:this={messagesEl}>
            {#each chat.messages as msg, i (i)}
                <li class="message {msg.role}">
                    {#if msg.role === 'partner'}
                        <div class="avatar-wrap">
                            <img src={chat.profilePicture} alt={chat.name} class="avatar" />
                        </div>
                    {/if}
                    <div class="bubble">
                        <span class="bubble-text">{msg.text}</span>
                        <span class="message-time">{formatTime(msg.time)}</span>
                    </div>
                </li>
            {/each}
        </ul>
    {/if}
</section>
```

**CSS highlights:**
- `.chat`: `display: flex; flex-direction: column;` ÔÇö parent handles `flex: 1; overflow-y: auto` via `:global(.chat)`
- `.chat-header`: `position: sticky; top: 0; flex-shrink: 0; background: white; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;` ÔÇö stays visible during scroll
- `.message-list`: `list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; padding: 8px;`
- `.message.user`: `justify-content: flex-end;` ÔÇö bubble right-aligned, no avatar
- `.message.partner`: `justify-content: flex-start;` ÔÇö avatar + bubble left-aligned
- `.message.user .bubble`: blue background (`#0084ff`), white text
- `.message.partner .bubble`: light gray (`#e9e9eb`), dark text
- Avatar/status-dot styles duplicated from Selector (Svelte scopes styles per component ÔÇö unavoidable without a shared CSS layer)

### 3. Write tests first (fail phase)

**`src/lib/Chat.svelte.spec.ts`** (new) ÔÇö write these before implementing Chat:

Test groups:
- **header**: partner name visible, avatar present, status dot present, status dot class matches partner status, status text visible
- **empty state**: `.empty-state` present when no messages, `.message-list` absent
- **messages**: all messages render, `.message.partner` count correct, `.message.user` count correct, partner messages include avatar, user messages do not, each message has `.message-time`
- **chat switching**: selecting a different chat updates the header name; messages from new chat appear

State setup pattern (from Selector tests):
```ts
beforeEach(() => {
    appState.currentlySelected = 0;
    appState.chats[0].messages = [];  // reset Claudia to clean state
});
```

**`src/routes/page.svelte.spec.ts`** ÔÇö update the heading check now (it already fails after Chat changes):
```ts
// Before (h2 will be gone):
await expect.element(page.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Claudia', level: 2 })).toBeInTheDocument();

// After:
await expect.element(page.getByText('Claudia')).toBeInTheDocument();
```

**Verify tests compile and fail** (`vitest run src/lib/Chat.svelte.spec.ts`) before proceeding.

### 4. Implement `Chat.svelte` (make tests pass)

Replace the stub with the full component described above. Run `vitest run` to confirm all tests green.

## Verification

1. **Tests pass**: `vitest run` ÔÇö Selector, page layout, and new Chat tests all green
2. **Visual check**: Ask user to start dev server and confirm:
   - Chat header shows "Claudia" with active status dot
   - Sending a message shows a right-aligned blue bubble
   - Selecting Jordan shows their seed message as a left-aligned gray bubble with avatar
   - New messages auto-scroll to bottom
3. **Update PPD**: Mark "Full message rendering" as complete

